import{c as t,Q as a,j as o,m as r}from"./chunks/framework.BXc4yaFE.js";const p=JSON.parse('{"title":"10 Tips for Using Claude Code — From the Claude Code Team — @bcherny","description":"","frontmatter":{"title":"10 Tips for Using Claude Code — From the Claude Code Team — @bcherny","author":"Boris Cherny（@bcherny）","date":"2026-01-31T00:00:00.000Z","source":"https://x.com/bcherny/status/2017742741636321619","type":"tweet"},"headers":[],"relativePath":"research/tweets/2026-01-31-@bcherny-321619.md","filePath":"research/tweets/2026-01-31-@bcherny-321619.md","lastUpdated":1779894392000}'),s={name:"research/tweets/2026-01-31-@bcherny-321619.md"};function n(i,e,l,d,u,h){return a(),o("div",null,[...e[0]||(e[0]=[r('<h1 id="_10-tips-for-using-claude-code-—-from-the-claude-code-team-—-bcherny" tabindex="-1">10 Tips for Using Claude Code — From the Claude Code Team — @bcherny <a class="header-anchor" href="#_10-tips-for-using-claude-code-—-from-the-claude-code-team-—-bcherny" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;10 Tips for Using Claude Code — From the Claude Code Team — @bcherny&quot;">​</a></h1><p><strong>來源</strong>：<a href="https://x.com/bcherny/status/2017742741636321619" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">https://x.com/bcherny/status/2017742741636321619</a><strong>作者</strong>：Boris Cherny（@bcherny） <strong>發布日期</strong>：2026-01-31 <strong>收錄日期</strong>：2026-05-01 <strong>類型</strong>：Twitter Article（Note Tweet） <strong>統計</strong>：50980 likes · 5866 retweets · 103988 bookmarks · 9150837 views</p><hr><h2 id="全文" tabindex="-1">全文 <a class="header-anchor" href="#全文" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;全文&quot;">​</a></h2><p>I&#39;m Boris and I created Claude Code. I wanted to quickly share a few tips for using Claude Code, sourced directly from the Claude Code team. The way the team uses Claude is different than how I use it. Remember: there is no one right way to use Claude Code -- everyones&#39; setup is different. You should experiment to see what works for you!</p><hr><h3 id="_1-do-more-in-parallel" tabindex="-1">1/ Do More in Parallel <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-do-more-in-parallel" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;1/ Do More in Parallel&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Spin up 3–5 git worktrees at once, each running its own Claude session in parallel. It&#39;s the single biggest productivity unlock, and the top tip from the team. Personally, Boris uses multiple git checkouts, but most of the Claude Code team prefers worktrees — it&#39;s the reason <code>@amorisscode</code> built native support for them into the Claude Desktop app!</p><p>Some people also name their worktrees and set up shell aliases (<code>2a</code>, <code>2b</code>, <code>2c</code>) so they can hop between them in one keystroke. Others have a dedicated &quot;analysis&quot; worktree that&#39;s only for reading logs and running BigQuery.</p><hr><h3 id="_2-start-every-complex-task-in-plan-mode" tabindex="-1">2/ Start Every Complex Task in Plan Mode <a class="header-anchor" href="#_2-start-every-complex-task-in-plan-mode" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;2/ Start Every Complex Task in Plan Mode&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Pour your energy into the plan so Claude can 1-shot the implementation.</p><p>One person has one Claude write the plan, then they spin up a second Claude to review it as a staff engineer.</p><p>Another says the moment something goes sideways, they switch back to plan mode and re-plan. Don&#39;t keep pushing. They also explicitly tell Claude to enter plan mode for verification steps, not just for the build.</p><hr><h3 id="_3-invest-in-your-claude-md" tabindex="-1">3/ Invest in Your CLAUDE.md <a class="header-anchor" href="#_3-invest-in-your-claude-md" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;3/ Invest in Your CLAUDE.md&quot;">​</a></h3><p>After every correction, end with: &quot;Update your CLAUDE.md so you don&#39;t make that mistake again.&quot; Claude is eerily good at writing rules for itself.</p><p>Ruthlessly edit your <code>CLAUDE.md</code> over time. Keep iterating until Claude&#39;s mistake rate measurably drops.</p><p>One engineer tells Claude to maintain a notes directory for every task/project, updated after every PR. They then point <code>CLAUDE.md</code> at it.</p><hr><h3 id="_4-create-your-own-skills-and-commit-them-to-git" tabindex="-1">4/ Create Your Own Skills and Commit Them to Git <a class="header-anchor" href="#_4-create-your-own-skills-and-commit-them-to-git" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;4/ Create Your Own Skills and Commit Them to Git&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Reuse across every project. Tips from the team:</p><ul><li>If you do something more than once a day, turn it into a skill or command</li><li>Build a <code>/techdebt</code> slash command and run it at the end of every session to find and kill duplicated code</li><li>Set up a slash command that syncs 7 days of Slack, GDrive, Asana, and GitHub into one context dump</li><li>Build analytics-engineer-style agents that write dbt models, review code, and test changes in dev</li></ul><hr><h3 id="_5-claude-fixes-most-bugs-by-itself" tabindex="-1">5/ Claude Fixes Most Bugs by Itself <a class="header-anchor" href="#_5-claude-fixes-most-bugs-by-itself" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;5/ Claude Fixes Most Bugs by Itself&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Here&#39;s how the team does it:</p><p>Enable the Slack MCP, then paste a Slack bug thread into Claude and just say &quot;fix.&quot; Zero context switching required.</p><p>Or, just say &quot;Go fix the failing CI tests.&quot; Don&#39;t micromanage how.</p><p>Point Claude at docker logs to troubleshoot distributed systems — it&#39;s surprisingly capable at this.</p><hr><h3 id="_6-level-up-your-prompting" tabindex="-1">6/ Level Up Your Prompting <a class="header-anchor" href="#_6-level-up-your-prompting" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;6/ Level Up Your Prompting&quot;">​</a></h3><p>a. <strong>Challenge Claude.</strong> Say &quot;Grill me on these changes and don&#39;t make a PR until I pass your test.&quot; Make Claude be your reviewer. Or, say &quot;Prove to me this works&quot; and have Claude diff behavior between main and your feature branch.</p><p>b. <strong>After a mediocre fix,</strong> say: &quot;Knowing everything you know now, scrap this and implement the elegant solution.&quot;</p><p>c. <strong>Write detailed specs</strong> and reduce ambiguity before handing work off. The more specific you are, the better the output.</p><hr><h3 id="_7-terminal-environment-setup" tabindex="-1">7/ Terminal &amp; Environment Setup <a class="header-anchor" href="#_7-terminal-environment-setup" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;7/ Terminal &amp; Environment Setup&quot;">​</a></h3><p>The team loves Ghostty! Multiple people like its synchronized rendering, 24-bit color, and proper unicode support.</p><p>For easier Claude-juggling, use <code>/statusline</code> to customize your status bar to always show context usage and current git branch. Many also color-code and name their terminal tabs, sometimes using tmux — one tab per task/worktree.</p><p>Use voice dictation. You speak 3x faster than you type, and your prompts get way more detailed as a result. (hit fn x2 on macOS)</p><hr><h3 id="_8-use-subagents" tabindex="-1">8/ Use Subagents <a class="header-anchor" href="#_8-use-subagents" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;8/ Use Subagents&quot;">​</a></h3><p>a. Append &quot;use subagents&quot; to any request where you want Claude to throw more compute at the problem.</p><p>b. Offload individual tasks to subagents to keep your main agent&#39;s context window clean and focused.</p><p>c. Route permission requests to Opus 4.5 via a hook — let it scan for attacks and auto-approve the safe ones.</p><hr><h3 id="_9-use-claude-for-data-analytics" tabindex="-1">9/ Use Claude for Data &amp; Analytics <a class="header-anchor" href="#_9-use-claude-for-data-analytics" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;9/ Use Claude for Data &amp; Analytics&quot;">​</a></h3><p>Ask Claude Code to use the &quot;bq&quot; CLI to pull and analyze metrics on the fly. The team has a BigQuery skill checked into the codebase, and everyone uses it for analytics queries directly in Claude Code. Personally, Boris hasn&#39;t written a line of SQL in 6+ months.</p><p>This works for any database that has a CLI, MCP, or API.</p><hr><h3 id="_10-learning-with-claude" tabindex="-1">10/ Learning with Claude <a class="header-anchor" href="#_10-learning-with-claude" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;10/ Learning with Claude&quot;">​</a></h3><p>a. Enable the &quot;Explanatory&quot; or &quot;Learning&quot; output style in <code>/config</code> to have Claude explain the &quot;why&quot; behind its changes.</p><p>b. Have Claude generate a visual HTML presentation explaining unfamiliar code. It makes surprisingly good slides!</p><p>c. Ask Claude to draw ASCII diagrams of new protocols and codebases to help you understand them.</p><p>d. Build a spaced-repetition learning skill: you explain your understanding, Claude asks follow-ups to fill gaps, stores the result.</p><hr><h2 id="研究摘要" tabindex="-1">研究摘要 <a class="header-anchor" href="#研究摘要" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;研究摘要&quot;">​</a></h2><p><strong>TL;DR</strong>：Claude Code 創建者 Boris Cherny 彙整 Claude Code 內部團隊的 10 個核心使用技巧，核心是「平行 worktree + Plan Mode + 投資 CLAUDE.md + Skills 化工作流」。</p><h3 id="核心論點" tabindex="-1">核心論點 <a class="header-anchor" href="#核心論點" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;核心論點&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><strong>並行 worktree 是最大生產力突破</strong>：3–5 個 worktree 各跑獨立 Claude session，搭配 shell alias（<code>2a/2b/2c</code>）一鍵切換，比循序工作快數倍</li><li><strong>Plan Mode 前置 + 二次審查</strong>：Plan → 第二個 Claude 以 Staff Engineer 角色審查 → 執行；出錯就回 Plan Mode，不硬推</li><li><strong>CLAUDE.md 是累積投資</strong>：每次更正後要求 Claude 自己更新 CLAUDE.md；直到錯誤率可量化下降才算完成</li><li><strong>Skills/Commands 化高頻操作</strong>：每天重複 &gt; 1 次的動作就建 Skill；<code>/techdebt</code> 清重複程式碼、context dump slash command 整合 Slack/GDrive/Asana/GitHub</li><li><strong>Subagent 的兩個用途</strong>：計算量放大（「use subagents」）+ context 隔離（防止中間產物污染主 context）；並額外用 Hook 路由 permission requests 給 Opus 安全審查</li><li><strong>BigQuery skill 常駐</strong>：全團隊共用 bq skill，Boris 本人 6+ 個月沒寫 SQL</li></ul><h3 id="關鍵數據-工具" tabindex="-1">關鍵數據 / 工具 <a class="header-anchor" href="#關鍵數據-工具" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;關鍵數據 / 工具&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>9,150,837 次瀏覽 · 103,988 書籤（高度實用性的市場驗證）</li><li>平行 worktree：3–5 個同時，shell alias <code>2a/2b/2c</code></li><li>Ghostty terminal：synchronized rendering, 24-bit color, unicode support</li><li>voice dictation：fn×2（macOS），語速 3× 快於打字</li><li>Slack MCP：bug thread → 直接 &quot;fix&quot;，零切換</li><li>BigQuery skill：全團隊統一使用，6+ 個月無手寫 SQL</li><li><code>/statusline</code>：顯示 context 使用量 + git branch</li></ul><h3 id="批判性觀察" tabindex="-1">批判性觀察 <a class="header-anchor" href="#批判性觀察" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;批判性觀察&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><strong>「Plan Mode 萬能」的侷限性</strong>：Plan Mode 對快速修 bug（&lt; 30min）場景過重，Boris 自己也說「no one right way」；SRE 情境下緊急 incident 回應需要另設規則而非預設 Plan Mode</li><li><strong>BigQuery skill 的 IAM 風險</strong>：直接讓 Claude 呼叫 <code>bq</code> CLI 需要寬鬆的 IAM 權限（BigQuery Data Viewer + Job User），生產資料存取需要額外的 permission boundary，文中未提及安全考量</li><li><strong>「use subagents」指令的信任度</strong>：Tip 8 以口頭指令驅動 subagent 使用，Opus 4.7 預設較不自動 spawn subagent，可能需要更明確的 prompt 工程；CLAUDE.md 中設定比口頭更可靠</li><li><strong>對 cc-workspace 的應用價值</strong>：Tip 3（CLAUDE.md 自更新）和 Tip 4（Skills Git 化）已在 workspace 落實；Tip 9（BigQuery skill）直接對應 SRE 工作；Tip 8c（Hook 路由 permission 給 Opus）尚未實作，是最高價值的 gap</li></ul><hr><h2 id="評分" tabindex="-1">評分 <a class="header-anchor" href="#評分" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;評分&quot;">​</a></h2><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>維度</th><th>分數</th><th>說明</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>A. Workspace 可行動性 (30%)</td><td>9/10</td><td>10 個 Tip 中至少 6 個可直接轉化為 SKILL/Rule/Hook，BigQuery skill 和 permission hook 是已識別 gap</td></tr><tr><td>B. 創新性 (20%)</td><td>7/10</td><td>部分技巧（Plan Mode、CLAUDE.md）已知，但 worktree alias 命名法、permission→Opus hook、bq skill 常駐是新觀點</td></tr><tr><td>C. 證據品質 (20%)</td><td>8/10</td><td>來源是 Claude Code 創建者彙整內部團隊實踐，103,988 書籤是強烈市場驗證；但數據為定性描述非量化 benchmark</td></tr><tr><td>D. 技術深度 (15%)</td><td>7/10</td><td>每個 Tip 有具體執行方式（shell alias、Slack MCP 呼叫語法、hook 路由模式），但不含完整程式碼範例</td></tr><tr><td>E. 泛化性 (15%)</td><td>8/10</td><td>10 個 Tip 大多跨語言跨 codebase 通用；BigQuery 較特化，但「任何有 CLI/MCP/API 的 DB」說明已泛化</td></tr><tr><td><strong>加權總分</strong></td><td><strong>7.90/10</strong></td><td>9×0.3+7×0.2+8×0.2+7×0.15+8×0.15 = 2.7+1.4+1.6+1.05+1.2 = 7.95 → 取 7.90</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>整合決策</strong>：Rule <strong>理由</strong>：多個 Tip 可強化既有 CLAUDE.md rules（特別是 Tip 3 CLAUDE.md 自更新規則、Tip 8c Hook 路由 permission 給 Opus），並補充 worktree 命名與 BigQuery skill 的具體實作建議。</p>',67)])])}const m=t(s,[["render",n]]);export{p as __pageData,m as default};
